File: A healthcare worker prepares to conduct a PCR COVID-19 test. AFP/Emmanuel Croset JOHANNESBURG - New COVID-19 infections have surged by 137-percent since last week. Health Minister, Joe Phaahla, says it's driven by Gauteng, KwaZulu-Natal and the Western Cape. READ: COVID-19 in SA: 4,954 new cases, two deaths The three provinces account for 85-percent of all cases. He's also concerned about the high positivity rate in the country.